      '<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Artemis Hospital is a multi-specialty hospital located in Gurugram. It was established in July 2007 by Apollo Tyres Ltd which is one of the leading tyre manufacturers in India. The hospital is spread over 9 acres and has 400 plus beds. Artemis hospital is the first JCI and NABH accredited Hospital in Gurgaon. It is designed as one of the most advanced hospitals in India and provides a depth of expertise in the spectrum of advanced medical &amp; surgical interventions, comprehensive mix of inpatient and outpatient services. The hospital has put modern technology in the hands of renowned doctors from across the country and abroad to set new standards in healthcare. The medical practices and procedures followed in Artemis Hospital are benchmarked against the best in the world. It provides top-notch services and warm and open patient centric environment. This has made it one of the most revered hospitals in the country.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Specialisation</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt">There are specialised departments in the Artemis Hospital including Urology treatment, spine surgery, gynaecology, endocrinology, haematology, gastroenterology, nephrology, cardiology and cardiac surgery, dental treatment, ENT surgery, obesity or bariatric surgery, general surgery, paediatrics and paediatric surgery, ophthalmology, orthopaedics, neurology and neurosurgery, cosmetic and plastic surgery, oncology and oncosurgery, dermatology, pulmonologist, rheumatology, IVF and infertility, emergency and trauma, fetal medicine, haematopoietic stem cell transplant, internal medicine, mental health and behavioural science, nutrition and dietetics.</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:11pt">Critical Care</span></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt">There&#39;s a department of Critical Care in the Artemis Hospital which provides sophisticated, compassionate, and expert care to critically ill patients admitted in the hospital. There&#39;s a multidisciplinary team approach including intensivists, critical care fellows, nurses, respiratory and physical therapists, pharmacists, nutrition specialists and social workers. The hospital provides patient care in two multidisciplinary ICUs with more than 65 beds which account for approximately 25% of the total number of beds at Artemis Hospital. The hospital also provides in-house consultant level coverage round the clock, seven days a week.</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Locality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Artemis Hospital is situation near Unitech Cyber Park, Sector 51, and Gurugram 122001. It is a 32 minute drive from the International Airport which is 19.5 kilometres away from the hospital. The nearest metro station is 4 kilometres away which take nearly 10 minutes to cover. Taxis are easily available on call. Top rated Hotels like Crown Plaza, Ramada, and The Park are 5-10 minutes drive away. The French Press, Food for Foodies, and Flavours 52 are some of the restaurants which are near to the hospital. Sultanpur Bird Sanctuary, Ambience Mall and Kingdom of Dreams are some of the places which you can explore nearby the hospital. Damdama Lake and Cyber Hub are some of the tourist attractions near the hospital. The hospital is close to shopping centres, medicine shops and the restaurants which serve international cuisine.</span></p>\r\n',
