    about_hospital:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">One of the largest integrated healthcare groups in the region, Apollo Hospital was India&rsquo;s first multi-specialty private sector hospital. It was opened in 1983 by Dr. Reddy who was inspired and determined to bring quality healthcare to India. The mission of the hospital is to bring healthcare of international standards within the reach of every individual and the hospital is committed to the achievement and maintenance of excellence in education, research and healthcare for the benefit of humanity. Apollo Hospital has adopted clinical excellence as an industry standard and it has been one of Apollo&rsquo;s greatest contributions to the world of healthcare in India. Apollo promises to keep India healthy and to provide quality healthcare which is affordable. The Apollo Hospitals completed its 30<sup>th</sup> year recently and wishes to for a future where the nation is healthy, where its people are fighting fit, and India emerges as the preferred global healthcare destination.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Specialisation </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The multiple centres of excellence established by the hospital include Anaesthesiology, Paediatric Sciences, Apollo Elder Care, Apollo Centre Of Genomic Medicine, Apollo Cosmetic Clinic, Apollo Health Check, Apollo Sugar, Bariatric &amp; Metabolic Surgery, Bone Marrow Transplant, Apollo Cancer Centre, Cardiac &amp; Cardiology, Dental Clinic, Dermatology, Dietetics &amp; Clinical Nutrition, Emergency Care, Endovascular Surgery, Endocrinology (Diabetes Care), ENT, Fetal Medicine, Gastroenterology &amp; Herpetology, Surgical Gastroenterology, General &amp; Advanced Laparoscopic Surgery, Gynaecology &amp; Obstetrics, Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy, IVE, Internal Medicine, Laboratory Services, Neonatology, Nephrology, Neurosciences, Nuclear Medicine, Ophthalmology, Orthopaedic, Paediatric Urology &amp; Paediatric Surgery, Physiotherapy &amp; Rehabilitation, Psychiatry &amp; Clinical Psychology, Radiology / Radio Diagnosis, Respiratory, Sleep Medicine &amp; Critical Care, Rheumatology, Robotic Surgery, Spine Surgery, Transfusion Medicine, Transplant, Urology &amp; Anthology.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Locality </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Apollo Hospitals, New Delhi is located at Mathura road, Sarita Vihar, New Delhi. Nearest to the hospital, lies the Delhi (DEL) airport at a distance of 19.3 kilometres which takes around 29 minutes to get to. The Jasola Apollo metro station is the nearest metro station with a distance of approximately 1 kilometre which is a 2 minute drive from the hospital. Kaisons Inn, Hotel Jasola Apollo and Fraser Suites New Delhi are some nearby located hotels. Nearest tourist attractions include India Gate, Gurudwara Bangla Sahib, Qutab Minar, Lotus Temple and Lodhi Garden. One could explore Pacific Mall and Living style Mall along with restaurants like Haldiram&rsquo;s, Subway, Zaika Express and The Kitchen Exotica as well.</p>\r\n',
