    hospital_city: "15",
    about_hospital:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">Fortis Hospital, Noida is a premier state-of-the-art facility hospital. It is one of the leading multispecialty hospitals that offer comprehensive medical care to every patient. It is the only corporate facility in Uttar Pradesh that covers an entire array of specialities from diagnostics to organ transplant (kidney &amp; liver). It caters to the special needs of patients and their families and is the second mega hub hospital, in the Fortis Healthcare group. The hospital has been designed and developed to deliver patient care with maximum warmth, ease and effectiveness. The hospital has become the prime tertiary healthcare Centre in the city since it began operations in 2004. The hospital addresses a wide range of healthcare needs and prides itself in performing many first procedures in India and U.P. The hospital is known for its high standards in excellence and cardiology and cardiac surgery amongst others. There is a team of professional and highly experienced cardiologists duly supported by the latest medical technology makes it possible to offer patients the best possible medical attention. The hospital has also emerged as one of the leading referral Centre for renal science across the country. It is equipped with a spacious state-of-the-art dialysis unit that minimises the risk of infection to ensure a safer dialysis process for our patients.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Critical Care</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Fortis Hospital Noida has a dedicated Critical Care Department which renders round the clock quality care to all patient groups ailing with any life-threatening or chronic disease conditions requiring life support therapy. Patients having dysfunctions or failure of one or more organ systems like pulmonary, cardiac, neurology, kidney and liver are admitted to the Intensive Care Unit (ICU). There is an expert multidisciplinary team which focuses on offering comprehensive care to all the ICU patients. The team comprises of well trained, skilled and highly efficient staff in critical care medicine. Fortis specializes in delivering utmost care and comfort for the patients suffering from&nbsp; major health problems including Respiratory failure, Major trauma, Severe burns, Organ transplants, Kidney failure, Sepsis and septic shock, Stroke. The hospital specializes in life support modality that is ECMO (Extracorporeal membrane Oxygenation) and ECMO retrieval services and ensures a higher doctor and nurse to patient ratio in ICU for complete patient satisfaction and safety by continuous staff monitoring for the speedy recovery of the patients.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Specialisation </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Fortis Hospital Noida has specialised departments for different conditions including Cardiology, Clinical Nutrition, Cosmetic, Reconstructive and Aesthetic Surgery, Dental, Dermatology, Diagnostics, Dialysis, Emergency and Trauma, Endocrinology, ENT, Gastroenterology and GI Surgery, General Surgery, Internal Medicine, IVF, Kidney Transplant, Liver Transplant,, Neonatology, Nephrology, Neurology, Obstetrics and Gynaecology, Oncology (medical, surgical, radiation therapy, bone marrow transplantation), Orthopaedics and joint replacement, Ophthalmology, Pain management, Paediatrics, Physiotherapy, Psychiatry, Psychology, Respiratory medicine / Pulmonology, Rheumatology, Thoracic surgery, Urology, Vascular Surgery. Fortis Noida has been committed to the delivery of world-class, holistic healthcare services.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Locality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Fortis Hospital is situated at B-22, Sector 62, Gautam Buddh Nagar, Noida, Uttar Pradesh 201301. It is 36 kilometres away from Indra Gandhi International Airport which takes around 43 minutes to cover by car. Noida City Center Station is the nearest metro station to the hospital and Anand Vihar and Ghaziabad Stations are the nearest railway stations. Top rated hotel, Hotel Luxury Suites is just 1.8 kilometre away from the hospital and Hotel Orange Pie is just 1.4 kilometre away. Treebo Trip Vizima, Dewdrop Ananya Suites, and Hotel Diamond are also near the hospital. The Hunger Cure, The Great Food Factory, Punjabi Darbar, and The Thali Deliver are some of the restaurants which are close to the hospital. You can explore National Science Centre, Nehru Park, and National Museum which are near the hospital. Safdarjung Tomb, India Gate, Qutub Minar, and Gurudwara Bangla Sahib are some of the tourist attractions which are close to the hospital.</p>\r\n',
