    about_hospital:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">Apollo Hospital, Ahmadabad is a tertiary care flagship unit of the Apollo Hospitals Group founded on the 11<sup>th</sup> of May 2003. Apollo Hospitals Enterprise Limited is an Indian multinational healthcare group. Apollo Hospital, Ahmadabad focuses on centres of excellence like Cardiac Sciences, Neuro Sciences, and Orthopaedics including Knee Replacement, Hip Replacement and Spine Surgery, Cancer, Emergency Medicine and Solid Organ Transplants besides the complete range of more than 35 allied medical disciplines under the same roof. The hospital provides holistic healthcare that includes prevention, treatment, rehabilitation and health education for patients, their families and clients by touching their lives. Apollo Hospitals has always kept its Patients First and strived to deliver the best care right from the infrastructure to the latest medical technology acquisition. It has become the preferred destination for international patients as it provides international standards of treatment and healthcare to their patients. The hospital is also the second hospital in the Apollo Hospitals Group, performing regular Stem Cell Transplant/Bone Marrow Transplant for various Haematological conditions. At least one transplant per month is performed in the hospital with over 90% success rate with regard to hospital discharges. Apollo Hospital Ahmadabad is the only hospital with a Radiation Oncology unit in the city. This unit has been established by CBCC which is a USA based cancer centre.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Critical Care</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Apollo Hospitals, Ahmadabad has one of the most advance, fully equipped intensive &amp; critical care departments. The hospital offers most advanced and state-of-art facilities in the region. Multiple ICUs such as Medical, Surgical, Cardiac, Cardiothoracic, HDU, Neonatal, and Transplant along with a Bronchoscopy unit, a pulmonary function laboratory and Sleep Lab which are managed by a team of highly qualified intensivists. The unit has a total of 23 beds, all equipped with latest monitoring facilities and medical devices to provide immediate and world class treatment for critically ill patients with varied medical conditions. It also has facilities to do complex diagnostic and therapeutic procedures. There are highly advance ventilators and excellent medical backup. Bedside ultrasound and other modalities like dialysis, cardiac pacing etc are also available in case of need. There are Transport Ventilators which are available to transfer patients of any severity to and fro from different hospitals and within hospital. There is a well equipped bronchoscopy unit which has both adult and paediatric video bronchoscope for trans-bronchial lung biopsies and needle aspiration whenever needed. The procedures are routinely done in various intensive care units as well when need arises.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Specialities</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Apollo Hospital Ahmadabad has specialised departments for different conditions which includes Gastroenterology, Transplant, Robotic surgery, Heart oncology, Orthopaedics, Emergency care, Neurology, Neurosurgery, Nephrology, Dermatology, Transfusion medicine, Ophthalmology, Obstetrics and&nbsp; Gynaecology, Allergy and Immunology, Plastic surgery, ENT, Nuclear medicine, Pulmonologist, Paediatrics, Urology, Pathology, Psychiatry, Microbiology lab, Internal medicine, Anaesthesiology, Physical medicine, Radiology, ICU, General surgery, Vascular and non-vascular intervention.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Locality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Apollo Hospital International Limited is situated at Plot No.1 A, Bhat GIDC Estate, Gandhinagar &ndash; 382428, Gujarat. It is just 6 kilometres away from the Ahmadabad International Airport which takes approximately 15 minutes to travel by road. The Apollo Hospital stop is the nearest one to Apollo Hospital in Ahmadabad. Ahmadabad JN is the closest railway station to the hospital which is exactly at a distance of 6..58 kilometres. Top rated Hotel, Hotel Le Grande Residency is just 0.8 kilometres away from the hospital and Hotel Radisson Blu is just 1 kilometre away. Hotel German Palace, Hotel Furaat Inn and Hotel Regenta Central Antarim are also near the hospital. Suruchi. The Food Court, Swadeshi Bhojanalaya, Mohan Ji Thaal and Radhe Fortune are some of the restaurants which are close to the hospital. You can explore Riverfront Flower Park, Bai Harir Vav ( Stepwell) and Auto World Vintage Car Museum which are near the hospital. Hutheesing Jain Temple, Shahi Jam-e-Masjid, ISKCON Ahmadabad - Sri Sri Radha Govindji Temple and Sabarmati Ashram are some of the tourist attractions which are close to the hospital.</p>\r\n',
