    about_hospital:
      '<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="background-color:white"><span style="color:black">Lilavati Hospital and Research Centre is a multi-speciality tertiary care hospital located in Mumbai, India. It was founded in the year 1997 by Late Shri Lilavati Kirtilal Mehta. The hospitals aims at giving treatment to both the national and international patient&rsquo;s at the reasonable rates. The hospital has nearly 300consultants along with 1800other staff members. The number Of patients are around 1500 on daily basis</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Specialisation</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">LilavatiHospital and Research Centre conducts many procedures like ultrasound , blood test, X-ray, and major treatment such as anaesthesiology<strong>, </strong>audiology and speech therapy, bariatric surgery, cardiology and cardio vascular thoracic surgery, chest medicine, corneal transplant<strong>, </strong>colorectal surgery, dental<strong>, </strong>dermo cosmetology, diabetology, endocrinology and endocrine surgery, ent, head and neck surgery, gastroenterology and gastrointestinal surgery, general surgery, gynaecology and obstetrics, haematology, hair transplant, headache and migration clinic</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Infectious diseases, internal medicine, lactation liver transplant, minimally invasive surgery, nephrology, neurology and neuro surgery, oncology and onco surgery, ophthalmology, orthopaedics, pain management, paediatrics and paediatric surgery, psychiatry, clinical psychology, neuropsychology, reconstructive ( plastic) surgery, rheumatology, sleep medicine, urology and andrology, vascular and endovascular surgery, Other branches include Arthroplasty, Fracture Plaster, Perimetry, Topography, IOL Master, Pachymetry, YAG Laser, Retina Laser, Licentious, Cataract, Cataract surgery, Phacoemulsification, Invitro fertilization, Obstetrics &amp; Gynecology, Keyhole Surgery, Operation Theatre, Trauma, Neuro Surgery, and Endoscopy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Critical Care</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Lilavati Hospital provides the best quality treatment to its patients and take care of the patients rights to the fullest. The Hospital offers friendly services and maintains a very good interaction with their patients and give them all the medical care needed at its best. The critical care unit of the Lilavati Hospital consist of total of 77 beds and the team of the critical care unit consists of chief intensivists,Junior intensivists, senior and junior doctor staff and well trained and professional nursing and paramedical staff.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li style="text-align:justify"><strong>Surgical intensive care unit</strong>consists of 12 beds that serves the cardiac and other surgical patients.</li>\r\n\t<li style="text-align:justify"><strong>Intensive critical care unit</strong> consists of 19 beds that serves the cardiac and non cardiac emergencies.</li>\r\n\t<li style="text-align:justify"><strong>Neonatal intensive care unit </strong>consists of 6 beds that provides per natal and postnatal care.</li>\r\n\t<li style="text-align:justify"><strong>Paediatric intensive care unit </strong>treats critically ill infants, children and adolescents upto 18 years of age.</li>\r\n\t<li style="text-align:justify"><strong>Day care Unit</strong> it provides treatment and care to the patients who are not required to be admitted to the hospital and stay overnight. It is located on the 8<sup>th</sup> floor of the hospital. All kinds of minor surgical procedure, intermediate and major surgical procedures such as cardiac catherization, cataract with IOL, lithotripsy are performed here.</li>\r\n\t<li style="text-align:justify"><strong>Diagnostic department </strong>It carried out test related to haematology, biochemistry, histopathology, clinical pathology, serology, immunology and microbiology. The department is open 24/7. It carried it tests for departments namely Pathology, Radiology and imaging, Urodynamics, Nuclear medicine, Non invasive cardiology, Home sample collection and other tests.</li>\r\n\t<li style="text-align:justify"><strong>Dialysis department </strong>It is situated on the 6<sup>th</sup> floor of the hospital building. Nearly 40 dialysis patients are given the treatment every day. The unit comprises of 25 machines for haemodialysis.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Locality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Lilavati Hospital is situated at A-791, Bandra Reclamation, Bandra West, and Mumbai 400050. India, It is around 15 minutes drive from the International Airport, Mumbai. And from the Bandra Railway Station, the hospital distance is around 2km that takes around 2-5 minutes to reach to the destination. Hospital is at 2 minutes walking distance from the nearest bus stopping. Top rated hotels like Hotel Taj land ends are nearly 1.2km away from the hospital.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Hotel Rang Sharda is nearly at 0.2km distance from the Hospital. One can explore Nehru Science centre and Dr. Bhau Daji Lad museum that are nearby the hospital. Bandra fort and Bandra sea view are nearby tourist places</p>\r\n',
