    hospital_city: "9",
    about_hospital:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">Jaslok Hospital and Research Centre is a private hospital located in Mumbai, Maharashtra. It was founded by Seth Lokoomal Chanrai, who was a philanthropist, along with surgeon Shantila lJamnadas Mehta. The name Jaslok is a combination of the names of Seth Lokoomal and his wife, Jasotibai. The hospital was inaugurated on 6 July 1973 by the erstwhile Prime Minister, Indra Gandhi. Jaslok Hospital and Research Centre is one of the oldest tertiary cares, multi-specialty trust hospitals in the country. The hospital has ongoing research activities in various fields in collaboration with other institutions in India and abroad. More importantly, the hospital has involved into a tertiary referral centre that provides a treatment for advanced, complex medical problems. Jaslok Hospital has all qualified nurses with many of them having additional qualification and specialisation.The hospital is also a training institution and it attracts patients not only from Mumbai but all parts of Maharashtra. The hospital is also a full-fledged teaching institution and conducts postgraduate courses being recognised by the National Board of Examinations in 22 specialties.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Specialisation </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Jaslok Hospital and Research Centre has many different medical specialisation such as Anaesthesiology, Assisted Reproduction (IVF), Audiology &amp; Speech Therapy, Bariatric Surgery, Cardiology, Cardio-Vascular &amp; Thoracic Surgery, Cardiovascular Thoracic Surgery, Clinical Psychology, Colorectal surgery, Critical Care, Dermatology, Dietetics and Nutrition, Endocrinology / Dialectology, ENT, Gastroenterology, Gastrointestinal Surgery, General and Laparoscopic Surgery, General Medicine, General Surgery, Genetics, Geriatric Medicine, Haematology, Hepatology, Imaging and Interventional Radiology, Infectious Disease, Laboratory Medicine, Liver Transplant, Medical Oncology, Microbiology, Molecular Pathology, Nephrology, Neurology, Neurosurgery , Nuclear Medicine, Nuclear Medicine, Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology,Ophthalmology, Oral &amp; Maxillofacial Surgery, Orthopaedic Surgery, Paediatrics, Pain Management, Psychiatry,Radiation,Oncology,RespiratoryDiseases,Rheumatology,RoboticSurgery,Spine Surgery,Surgical Oncology, Urology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The hospital also has specialised clinics such as Ankylosing Spondylitis &amp; Psoriatic Clinic, Assisted Reproduction (IVF) Clinic, Bladder clinic for children, Endometriosis Clinic, Epilepsy Clinic, Headache Clinic, Heart Failure Clinic, Hepatology, Gastroenterology &amp; Liver Clinic, Lighthouse Clinic, Multidisciplinary Clinics (MDCC),Neuropsychiatry Clinic, Paediatric Liver Clinic, Paediatric Nephrology Clinic, Paediatric Rheumatology Clinic, Pelvic Floor Clinic (Urology, Colorectal Surgery, Gynaecology), Spasticity Clinic, Sports Injury Clinic, Varicose Vein Clinic</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Critical Care</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The department of Critical Care at the Jaslok Hospital provides world class emergency care. It is available 24/7 to patients in potentially life threatening conditions which require life support system and other medical interventions. There is a multi-disciplinary team of critical care specialists which provide broad-ranging consultative, diagnostic and therapeutic services for patients who have life threatening conditions. The hospital provides full spectrum of ICU and Critical Care Unit (CCU) services by specially-trained, efficient and skilled physicians. Critical Care Medicine at Jaslok Hospital represents state of the art, 48 bed ICU with 5 ICU chambers all dedicated to provide the highest level of quality care to different kinds of patients.The hospital also has separate ICU for Cardiac patients, Neuro patients, Oncology patients and Orthopaedic surgery patients in order to avoid any chances of infection. There&#39;s an ECMO team which is operational 24X7 which is unique because very few hospitals have this kind of facility in Mumbai.Jaslok Hospital has treated the most difficult cases from the city which many hospitals refuse to even admit which gives them a second life. Advanced hemodynamic monitoring, ventilation, CRRT, SLED, ECMO, imaging, IABP, invasive procedures, bronchoscopy, etc as per the requirement of the patient is ready in the ICU with dedicated intensives and expert consultation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Locality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Jaslok Hospital and Research Centre is situated at 15 - Dr. Deshmukh Marg, Pedder Road, IT colony, Tardeo.Mumbai - 400026.It&#39;s a 25 minute drive from the International Airport which is at a distance of 14 kilometres. The Grant Road station is the nearest one to Jaslok Hospital. It takes 3 minutes to travel from Grant Road Station (w) to Jaslok Hospital. Approximate driving distance between Grant Road Station (w) and Jaslok Hospital is 3 kilometres. The hospital is at 2 minutes walking distance from the nearest bus stopping. Top rated Hotel, Hotel Four Seasons is 2.7 kilometres from Jaslok Hospital and Hotel Kemps Corner is 0.2 kilometres away. One can explore Mani Bhawan Gandhi Museum and Babulnath Temple which are near the hospital. Malabar Hills and The National Museum of Indian Cinema are the nearby tourist places. Sun restaurant, Kailash Parbat and China Garden are some of the restaurants which are close to the hospital. Ghatkopar Metro Station is the nearest metro station to Jaslok Hospital which is 11 kilometres away.</p>\r\n',
