    about_hospital:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">Nanavati Max Super Speciality Hospital formerly known as Dr. Balabhai Nanavati Hospital is a private hospital located in Mumbai, India. The hospital was founded by Ratilal Manilal Nanavati. It was inaugurated by India&rsquo;s first Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru in 1950. The hospital has been opened for 70 years now.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Specialisation </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">There are many specialised treatment programmes in the hospital such as Breast Cancer Program, Head, Face and Neck Cancer Program, Gynaecological Oncology Program, Urological Cancer Program, Lymphoma Cancer Program, Paediatric Cancer Program, Medical Oncology Program, Hepatobiliary Pancreatic Oncology Program, HIPEC Technology, Gastrointestinal Cancer program, Radiation Oncology, Hip Replacement Unit, Arthroscopy and Sports Medicine, Hemato-Oncology&amp; Bone Marrow Transplant, Sports Injury Unit, Centre for Joint Replacement, Knee Replacement Unit, Orthopaedic Rehabilitation Clinic, Spine Surgery Unit, Centre For Orthopaedics, Trauma Care Unit, Autologous Transplant, Allogeneic Transplant, Microscopic / Endoscopic Disc, Surgery Unit, Spine Fusion Surgery Unit, Back Pain Management Unit, Advanced Aneurysm Treatment Unit, Neuro-Endoscopy Surgery Unit, Stroke Unit, Neuro Electrophysiology Unit, Centre of Spine Surgery, Parkinsons Movement Disorder, Invasive Interventional Cardiology Unit, Cardiothoracic and Vascular Surgery Unit, CAG &amp; PTCA Unit, Arrhythmia Services, Kidney Dialysis Centre, Kidney Transplant Unit, Kidney Stone Clinic, Urological Surgeries Unit, Centre For Aesthetic (Cosmetic)surgery, Hair Transplant Clinic, Reconstructive Plastic Surgery, HPB malignancies, Liver DiseasesUnit, Liver Transplant Unit, Acute Liver Failure Unit, Neonatal Intensive Care Unit, Medical Intensive Care Unit, Surgical Intensive Care Unit, Cardiac Intensive Care Unit (CICU), Neurosciences Intensive Care Unit (CCU 4), Organ Transplant Intensive Care Unit (CCU 4), Paediatric intensive care unit, Interventional PulmonologyUnit, Pulmonary Function Testing Unit, SleepApnea Clinic, Asthma &amp; Allergy Unit General Paediatrics Unit, Paediatric Surgery &amp; Urology Unit, Neonatology and Neonatal Intensive Care Unit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">There are many different specialised departments in the hospital such as Accidental and Emergency Centre, Anaesthesiology, Pain Management, Dermatology, Endocrinology, Gynaecology &amp; Obstetrics, Laboratory Medicine (Pathology), Mental Health (Psychiatry, Psychology), Nutrition and Dietetics, Nuclear Medicine, ENT, Physiotherapy, Transfusion Medicine (Blood Bank), Hand &amp; Foot Clinic, Movement Disorder Clinic, Sleep Apnea Clinic, Ayurveda, Bariatric Surgery General &amp; Minimal Access Surgery, Radiology, Internal Medicine, Ophthalmology, Dentistry, Telemedicine.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Locality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Balabhai Nanavati Hospital is situated at S V Road, Vile Parle (West), Mumbai 400056, Maharashtra. It is a 10 minute drive from the International Airport, Mumbai which is just 6 Kilometres away. Andheri Station is the nearest Railway Station which is 3.5 kilometres away from the hospital. It takes around 12-15 minutes to cover the distance. The hospital is at 2 minutes walking distance from the nearest bus stopping. Top rated hotel, Hotel the Orchid is 1.61 kilometres away and Hotel Parle International is just 0.82 kilometres away from the hospital. One can explore Dolphin Aquarium and VR Game zone which are near the hospital. Juhu Beach, Sarovar Farmhouse, and Parla Jin Mandir are some of the tourist attractions near the hospital. Grass Hopper Restaurant, Lean Meal Co, Moonlight Caf&eacute;, and Walk N Hog are some of the restaurants which are near to the hospital. D N Nagar Metro station is the nearest metro station to the Dr. Balabhai Nanavati Hospital.</p>\r\n',
