    about_hospital:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">LH Hiranandani Hospital is a public charitable trust hospital in Mumbai, Maharashtra, India. It was founded in honour of Padma Bhushan, Dr L H Hiranandani in February 2004. Every kind of surgical procedure, simple or the most complex ones are performed at this hospital. The hospital is equipped with medical equipments which are purchased from the top-tier vendors in the world. Dr L H Hiranandani Hospital has grown from a 130 bed hospital to a 240 bed facility within a short span of time.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Specialisation </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">In Dr L H Hiranandani Hospital, various different types of surgeries are performed such as Bariatric, Obesity and Metabolic Surgery, Cardiovascular Thoraic Surgery, ENT, Liver Transplant and Surgery, Minimally Invasive &amp; General Surgery, Neurosurgery, Ophthalmology, Orthopaedics, Pediatric Surgery, Reconstructive Surgery, Urology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The hospital also has specialised clinics such as Elder Care Clinic, Allergy-Asthma Clinic, Breathe Well Clinic, Diabetic Foot Clinic, Fatty Liver Clinic, High Risk OPD on Paediatric Evaluation (H.O.P E), High Risk Pregnancy Clinic, Metabolic Clinic - Diabetes and Obesity Centre of Excellence, Home quarantine package, Nerve &amp; Muscle Clinic, Post COVID Clinic, Pain Clinic, Rheumatology, Sleep Medicine, Sports Medicine Clinic, Stress Urinary Incontinence Clinic, Vertigo Clinic, Voice &amp; Swallowing Clinic</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">There&rsquo;s a specialisation of medicine in Dr L H Hiranandani Hospital such as Anaesthesia, Cardiology, Critical Care, Endocrinology / Diabetology, Gastroenterology, General Medicine, Neonatology, Nephrology, Neurology, Paediatrics, Psychiatry, and Pulmonology.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Locality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">L H Hiranandani Hospital is situated at Hill Side Avenue, Hiranandani Gardens, Powai, and Mumbai 400076. It&#39;s a 20 minute drive from the International Airport, Mumbai. The distance from the Kanjur Murg railway station is 3.4 kilometres which takes around 10-12 minutes. The hospital is at 2 minutes walking distance from the nearest bus stopping. Top rated Hotel, Hotel Rodas is 0.62 kilometres away from the hospital and Hotel the Westin is 2.28 kilometres away. One can explore Hare-Krishna Art Studio and MCGM Hiranandani Gardens which are near the Hospital. Powai Lake and Suvarna Temple are the nearby tourist places. Mirchi and Mime, Sigree Global Grill, and Mantra Dining Bar and some of the restaurants close to the hospital. Jagruta Nagar Metro station is the nearest metro station to the Dr L H Hiranandani Hospital.</p>\r\n',
