    about_hospital:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital and Medical Research Institute is a tertiary-care hospital located in Mumbai, India. It was opened in the year 2009 and is named after Kokilaben Ambani, wife of industrialist Dhirubhai Ambani.The hospital emphasis on excellence in clinical services, diagnostic facilities, and research. Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital has boasted of many firsts not only in India but also in Asia. This hospital has the first 3-room intra-operative MRI suite (IMRIS) in Asia, Asia&rsquo;s first EDGE radio surgery system from Varian Medical Systems, India&rsquo;s first Spine Surgery Suite featuring the O-arm and many more.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Specialisation </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital has many speciality departments such as Anaesthesiology, Clinical Haematology, Dental Surgery, Dermatology,Development Disorders, Endocrinology &amp; Diabetes, ENT, Foetal Medicine, Gastroenterology, General Surgery,Genetics and Molecular Medicine, Internal Medicine, Interventional Radiology, Laboratory Medicine, Minimal Access Surgeries (MAS), Nephrology, Nuclear Medicine, Ophthalmology, Psychiatry, Pulmonary Medicine, Regenerative Medicine (Stem Cells), Radiology, Reproductive Endocrinology and Infertility (IVF), Transfusion Medicine (Blood Bank)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The hospital also has many super special clinics such asAlzheimer&#39;s Clinic, Autism Clinic, Bedwetting Clinic &ndash; Children, Breast Clinic, Cerebral Palsy Clinic, De-addiction Clinic, Diabetic Foot Clinic, Endometriosis Clinic, Geriatric Clinic, Glaucoma Clinic, Heart Failure Clinic, Incontinence Clinic, Kidney Stone Clinic, Osteoporosis Clinic, Pain Clinic, Parkinson&#39;s Clinic, Pulmonary Hypertension Clinic, Sleep Apnea Clinic, Smoking Cessation Clinic, Stress Incontinence Clinic, Stroke Clinic,Travel Clinic, Varicose Vein Clinic, Voice Clinic, and Wilson&#39;s Disease Clinic.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Critical Care</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital has the largest number of critical care beds in Mumbai, with 180 ICU beds. The ICUs also have special technical features including ceiling-mounted, dual-arm pendants, which insure that the space around the patient is not cluttered. Another unique feature is dedicated air supply that helps in keeping the critical care area free of any kind of infection. There&#39;s a technology called Locomat Pro, a Robotic-driven Gait Orthosis and Computer-enhanced Rehabilitation device which helps in improving the walk in neurologically impaired patients.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Locality</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Kokilaben Dhirubhai Ambani Hospital is situated at Rao Saheb, Four Bungalows, Andheri West, Mumbai, and Maharashtra 400053. It is a15 minute drive from the International Airport, Mumbai. The distance from Andheri station is 10 KMwhich takes around 5-10 minutes. The hospital is at 2 minutes walking distance from the nearest bus stopping. The top rated Hotel Ramada Plaza is 4.5 kilometres away from the hospital and Hotel JW Marriott is 4.3 kilometres away. One can explore Silver Beach and ISKCON temple that are nearby the hospital. Gateway of India and Marine Drive are nearby tourist places.Red Chillies Taste of India, Quarterdeck Restro and bar, and O15s Caf&eacute; is some of the restaurants which are nearby the hospital. The nearest metro station to Kokilaben Hospital is Versova Metro Station. The distance between the hospital and Versova Metro Station is 650 meters only. It requires only 10-12 minutes if you cover the distance on foot.</p>\r\n',
