      '<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Accredited with NABH and NABL (ISQUA).</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">ISO 9001:2008 certified for all comprehensive protocols including clinical, nursing, diagnostics and allied areas.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Accredited with the AAHRPP Accreditation (Association for the Accreditation of the Human Research Protection Programs).</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Rated the Most Patient Recommended Hospital in India by the Consumer Voice.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Ranked as the Best Hospital in Bangalore for the past 8 years by The Week Magazine.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Ranked as the Best Hospital in Bangalore for the past 8 years by The Week Magazine.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Won the prestigious Golden Peacock National Quality Award 2005 in the Service category.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',
    facilities:
      '<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The hospital offers Manipal Ambulance Response Services (MARS) provides 360-degree pre-hospital care. The Ambulances come with critical life-saving equipment like ventilators, monitors, inbuilt ECG machines and other equipment which helps to monitor critical patients. The emergency team is Basic Life Support certified that gives the first help and stabilizes patient in ambulance. There is also a central monitoring system to relay LIVE information about the patient&#39;s condition directly to ALS trained emergency response centre physician. The primary aim is to make optimum use of the initial golden hour in an emergency.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The hospital provides affordable healthcare services to the privileged section through their association with Manipal Foundation and various Non-government organizations.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Ample parking space, a large cafeteria, and the spacious available for visitors.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The hospital is equipped with rooms and wards designed specifically to improve the comfort of patients and caretakers.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Manipal Hospital Bangalore, Old Airport Road is equipped with 600 beds and has over 60 specialities under one roof. There are a total of 144 intensive care beds amongst ICUs, ICCUs, NICUs and 20 modular State of the Art operation theatres with modern facilities. The imaging department is well equipped with 128 slice CT scan, 3 Tesla MRI, Bone densitometry, Digital mammography and the latest technology in PET CT.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Manipal north side Hospital Bangalore, Malleshwaram is equipped with 83 beds. The hospital also has an independent outpatient clinic which renders all services and health checks. </span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr Malathi Manipal Hospital Bangalore Jayanagar is equipped with 70 beds. </span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Manipal Hospital Whitefield is equipped with 284 beds. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',
