    about_hospital:
      '<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Apollo Hospital in Hyderabad&#39;s Jubilee Hills is a 400-bed tertiary care facility. It encompasses more than 50 medical and surgical specialties. The hospital has a built-up area of 190,000 square feet and is located on a 35-acre site. Its services are backed up by cutting-edge technology and skilled medical personnel. The vast majority of the hospital&#39;s consultants have worldwide experience, either educationally, professionally, or by observation. The hospital&#39;s average staff-to-patient ratio is 3:1, with a 1:1 ratio in high-volume sections such as the Intensive Care Unit and Cardiac Care Unit. After nearly 3 years, Apollo Hospitals, Jubilee Hills has evolved as Asia&#39;s most recognised and trusted integrated health city, focusing in the complete spectrum from sickness to wellness and holistic therapy. The hospital receives a large number of pharmacy walk-ins, admissions, emergency cases, and wellness consultations each day. Every second spent at the hospital, devoted doctors and personnel provide a variety of services such as CT scans, MRIs, Cardiac Surgeries, Dialysis procedures, organ transplants, and more, all at a fraction of worldwide charges. In one huge campus, Apollo Health City &ndash; Jubilee Hills offers education, research, telemedicine, medical device innovation, disease management programmes, med skills, and state-of-the-art physical medicine, rehabilitation, and wellness services. The hospital is propelled by dedicated personnel that go above and beyond to deliver excellent medical treatment. The medical staffs take a humanised approach to therapy, which helps patients feel less stressed and anxious about their care. The hospital&rsquo;s centre of excellence provides a one-stop solution for patients with multiple and complex medical problems, saving them time, effort, and money by eliminating the need to see many doctors and perform diagnostic tests to pinpoint their condition.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Specialisation </strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Apollo Hospital, Jubilee Hills has specialised departments for various different conditions including Cardiology, orthopaedics, ENT, Cancer Care, Gastroenterology, Neurosciences, Transplants, Pulmonologist, Critical Care, Bariatric surgery, Emergency, Robotic Surgery, Preventive Health Checks, Apollo Cosmetic, Apollo Eye, Bio-Medical Waste Data, Anaesthesia &amp; Intensive Care, Apollo Prostate, Day Care Specialists.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Critical Care</strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt">The critical care unit of Apollo Hospitals Jubilee Hills is one of the country largest. From molecular biology to sophisticated neurosurgery, the campus is essentially a health city, with every possible specialty and area of medicine covered. The critical care units are state-of-the-art and highly advanced. They have specialised equipment for each patient to ensure that key indicators are constantly monitored. Doctors with worldwide experience and certifications, as well as outstanding nurses and support staff, work as a cohesive team to provide the best world-class care possible. The drive and scientific approach to care at Apollo Hospitals Jubilee Hills has catalysed several modern medical miracles. As a tertiary care centre, it has specialists available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week to meet the needs of patients who travel from all over India and other continents such as Africa, Europe, Australia, and North America. Special services for overseas patients, such as the immediate availability of translators for languages like as Arabic, allow keep both the patient and the family informed and comfortable at all times. For the care of severe situations, the Intensive Care Unit in Hyderabad contains a wide range of advanced medical equipment. Aside from that, there is a team of well-trained nurses that are dedicated to giving patients an excellent bedside treatment. The dedicated staffs of pharmacists, nutritionists, physiotherapists, psychologists, and volunteers support the critical care unit.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Locality </strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Apollo Hospital is located at Road No 72 Opposite Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan School Film Nagar, Jubilee Hills, Hyderabad, Telangana 500033. It is 33 kilometres away from the Hyderabad International Airport which takes approximately 50 minutes to cover by car. Jubilee Hills stop is the nearest bus stop to the hospital. Jubilee Hills Check post is the nearest metro station to the hospital and Secunderabad Junction is the nearest railway station. Top rated hotel, Hotel Stay Jubilee Hills is just an 8 minute walk from the hospital. Taj Mahal Hotel, Mango Suits, Park Hyatt, and Star Inn Guess House are also close the hospital. Absolute Barbecue, Prost Brew, Tatva, and Barbecue Nation are some of the restaurants which are near the hospital. You can explore Lotus Pond, Hare Krishna Golden Temple, Jalagam Vengal Rao Park, and GVK One Mall which are close to the hospital. Charminar, Birla Mandir, Jala Vihar, and Chowmahalla Palace are some of the tourist attractions which are near the hospital.</span></p>\r\n',
