      '<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Apollo Health City, Jubilee Hills is a 33-acre facility with lush green grounds and a welcoming atmosphere for both patients and tourists.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">&nbsp;The campus is buzzing with doctors, nurses, students, IT workers, and patients for its many education, research, wellness, healthcare services, and IT programmes.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">&nbsp;The campus also offers Food &amp; Beverages, Department location, and Inpatient Accommodation.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The hospital is equipped with 400 beds and in the basement it offers services like Blood Bank, Labs (Microbiology, Histopathology, Biochemistry and Hematology), Hospital Information Management (Medical Records), Information Technology, Guest Dining Hall, Kitchen / pantry, and Medical Social Worker. </span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">On the ground floor of the hospital, there is an Emergency Room, Ambulance Service, Reception, Registration and Admission, IP / OP Billing, and 24 Hour Pharmacy.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">On the first floor, there is an Operation theatre complex, Intensive care units (SICU, Neuro ICU, CT Post, Neonatal Unit, PICU), and Nephrology Unit (Dialysis and KTU).</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">MICU, Super Deluxe Suites, and Office of General Manager &ndash; Operations are on the second floor of the hospital. </span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11.0pt">On the third and fourth floor there is a CCTV Ward, A Conference Hall, Library, and a Biomedical Department.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',
