    about_hospital:
      '<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Apollo Healthcare was established established by Dr Prathap C Reddy in 1983. It has a robust presence across the healthcare ecosystem. The chain has the largest network of the world&rsquo;s finest and brightest medical experts who provide compassionate care using outstanding expertise and advanced technology. It has been the pioneer in bringing ground-breaking healthcare technologies to India. Apollo Hospitals has consistently led game-changing developments in by bringing to the people, the latest innovations in key medical specialities. Apollo hospital Chennai is one of the best hospitals for heart care in India. It is the first Indian hospital to introduce techniques in coronary angioplasty, stereotactic radiotherapy and radio-surgery (for brain tumours).The hospital is also declared as the &#39;Centre of Excellence&#39; by the Government of India.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Specialisation</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Apollo Hospital Chennai has specialised departments for different conditions which includes Endocrinology, Gastroenterology, Vascular Surgery, Transplant Surgery, Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery, Gynecology, Dental Treatment, ENT Surgery, Obesity Or Bariatric Surgery, General Surgery, Cosmetic And Plastic Surgery, Oncology And Oncosurgery, Hematology, Nephrology, Urology Treatment, Neurology And Neurosurgery, And Orthopedics. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Critical Care</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Apollo hospital is one of the best critical care hospitals in India. Critical care is a crucial medical specialty caring for patients who are critically ill. These patients require support for instability (hypertension/hypotension), airway or respiratory compromise (ventilator support), acute renal failure, cardiac arrhythmias, or the cumulative effects of multiple organ failure, more commonly referred to now as multiple organ dysfunction syndrome. The patients who need intensive/invasive monitoring, such as in the crucial hours after major surgery or patients who are considered too unstable to transfer to a less intensively monitored unit may also be placed in the intensive care units. The critical care department at Apollo Hospitals, India is a combination of many specialties and technologies, offering the possibility of survival to patients who are acutely and critically ill. There is a 24-hour critical care unit which is a combination of multidisciplinary ICUS as well as ICUS dedicated to post cardiac surgery patients, stroke patients, post-transplant patients, as well as special ICUs for neonates and paediatric cases. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Locality</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Apollo Hospital Chennai is located at Greams Lane, 21, Greams Road, Thousand Lights, Chennai, Tamil Nadu, 60006. It is 17 kilometres away from the Airport which takes approximately 45 minutes to travel. The Grams Road bus stop is the nearest bus stop to the hospital which is at just 1 minute of walking distance. The hospital is reachable from all parts of Chennai. Top rated Hotel, Hotel Sky Gate is just at a distance of 850 metres from the hospital and Hotel Convastay Gajel is just 660 metres away. Hotel Sea Shell Residency, Hannu Reddy Residency and Hotel Century Courtyard are also near the hospital. New Bengali Mess, Savoury Sea Shell, Tibb&rsquo;s Frankie and Le Bistro are some of the restaurants which are close to the hospital. You can explore Anjaneyar Temple, Semmozhi Poonga, and Arignar Anna Zoological Park which are near the hospital. Dr. Br Ambedkar Statue, Marina Beach, Besant Nagar Beach and MGR Memorial are some of the tourist attractions which are near the hospital.</span></p>\r\n',
