    id: 28,
    hospital_name: "Yashoda Hospital, Hyderabad",
    hospital_city: "10",
    about_hospital:
      '<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt">Yashoda hospital is a multi-speciality hospital in Hyderabad, India. It was established by Dr. G. Surender Rao in 1989 as a small clinic and now it is ISO certified and the laboratories and facilities are accredited by NABL and NABH. It is of the best cancer hospitals in India, which has been treating 16,000 new cancer patients every year and also, it was the first hospital to implement 4D gated Rapid Arc for the treatment of moving tumors. Yashoda Hospital has many &lsquo;firsts&rsquo; including first inter-state heart transplantation in the region, first in the world to use Rapid Arc based Stereotactic radio-surgery, and treated world&rsquo;s largest number of cancer patients with Rapid Arc Technology. It has evolved as a centre of excellence in medicine providing the highest quality standards of medical treatment to all sections of the society. The team of doctors in this hospital is board certified, experienced in wide range of subspecialties and passionate about improving patient care. It includes skilled professionals who excel in clinical and surgical skills of advanced procedures that benefit the patients by minimal pain and discomfort, less time in the hospital, faster recovery period, and quicker resumption of your regular routines in life, less scarring and elimination of many potential complications from conventional surgery. The team ensures that patient&rsquo;s physical, mental and support systems are working together to produce a holistic outcome.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Specialisation </strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Yashoda Hospital has specialised departments for different conditions including Arthroscopy &amp; Sports</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Medicine, Bariatric Surgery, Cancer, Cardiology, Critical Care, CT Surgery, Dermatology, Emergency Services, Endocrinology, ENT, Medical Gastroenterology, General Medicine, Gynaecology, Hematology &amp; BMT, Interventional Radiology, Kidney Transplant, Liver Transplant, Heart &amp; Lung Transplant, Multi organ Transplant, Nephrology, Neurosciences, Nuclear Medicine, Ophthalmology, Orthopaedics, Pain. Management, Paediatrics, Paediatric Surgery, Physiotherapy, Plastic Surgery, Pulmonology, Radiology, Rheumatology, Robotic Science, Spine Surgery, Surgical, Gastroenterology, Thoracic Surgery, Urology, Vascular Surgery.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Critical Care</strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Yashoda Hospital is one of the best critical care hospitals in India. Critical care is a vital medical speciality that deals with critically ill and severely unwell patients. These patients require assistance with hypertension/hypotension, airway or breathing compromise (ventilator support), acute renal failure, cardiac arrhythmias, or the cumulative effects of multiple organ failure, sometimes known as multiple organ dysfunction syndromes. Patients, intensive/invasive monitoring such as in the critical hours following major surgery or who are deemed too unstable to be transferred to a less intensively monitored ward, may be admitted to intensive care units. The critical care department of Yashoda Hospital in India combines numerous specialisations and technology to give patients who are acutely or critically sick the best chance of survival. There is a 24-hour service available.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><strong>Locality</strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Yashoda Hospital is located at Raj Bhavan Road, Somajiguda, Matha Nagar, and Hyderabad 500082. It is at a distance of 7 kilometres from the Hyderabad Airport which takes approximately 15 minutes to cover by car. Necklace Road is the nearest bus stop to the hospital and Khairatabad Station is the nearest railway station. Irrum Manzil station is the nearest Metro Station to the hospital. Top rated hotel, Hotel Our Nest is just 560 metres away from the hospital and Hotel Grand Marvel Residency is just 90 metres away. Katriya Hotels and Towers, Hotel Inner Circle, and Hotel Virat Inn are also close to the hospital. Annapoorna Darshini, Nizami Grills, Swathi Tiffins, and Sai Ram Mess are some of the restaurants which are near the hospital. You can explore NTR Gardens, Buddha Statue, Sanjeevaiah Park, and Nizamia Observatory which are near the hospital. Charminar Fort, Khairatunneesa Tomb, and Tank Bund Lake are some of the tourist attractions which are close to the hospital.</span></p>\r\n',
