    facilities:
      '<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The CARE Hospitals, Banjara Hills, Hyderabad, has a 24-hour, state-of-the-art medical centre Emergency Unit, which caters to all types of accidents, victims and emergency cases. Equipped with the latest infrastructure, they have medical supplies available at all times from the 24-hour in-house pharmacy as well as blood from the NABH accredited Blood Bank. The hospital has highly experienced doctors and other medical staff&mdash; from providing urgent medical or surgical care, to comforting the patients and their care-givers or providing basic and advanced life support.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The hospital started its own Blood Bank in October 2002 in order to balance the variations between and the increased number of patients and the blood required. Currently, the Blood Bank contributes around 1000 units of blood per month. It also provides blood for cardiac surgeries and therapy. Storing, processing and banking blood are the activities performed through the bank. Tests like post donation screening tests, Rh titre, Coombs test, cold and warm antibodies, blood grouping and typing as well as haemoglobin tests for blood donors are conducted by the bank. The Cross-matching tests are performed by automated gel technology.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The ACLS ambulances of CARE Hospitals, Banjara Hills, are fully equipped with defibrillators, monitors, ventilators, suction machines, oxygen, drugs; etc. The emergency call number is 105711. It can be accessed by any landline or mobile number within the city and is a 24*7, free service, operated from the Emergency Room of the hospital. Dedicated paramedical staffs manage the ambulance service all the time. The best pre-hospital care for all the emergency calls received is provided by our Emergency Care unit. Well trained emergency medical technologists and driver&rsquo;s who provide pre-hospital care at home, and route to the hospital, man the ambulances. The Emergency Medical Technicians, who work under the guidance of the emergency physician, are highly experienced and knowledgeable and have skills of emergency management.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The hospital has a 24x7 pharmacy unit with qualified &amp; trained pharmacists. These are the people who help you with the instructions outlined in the prescriptions. The many advantages of buying medicines at the CARE Hospitals Pharmacy include- no scope for spurious drugs, expired medicines and substitution, storage of medicines as is specified, stocking of drugs according to the prescribed temperature standard whichhelps in retaining the quality and effectiveness, availability of abroad range of medicines, surgical, disposables, ARV, anti-cancer, life saving and general healthcare products, no waiting time, proper display of batch numbers, price &amp;expiry and a computerised billing system.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">The Department of Laboratory Medicine consists of the disciplines of Haematology, Pathology, Microbiology and Clinical Biochemistry. This Department provides the qualitative analysis of biological fluids like blood, serum or plasma, tissue, urine and stool for specific constituents to support clinicians in the practice of medicine. State-of-the-art equipment is available in the laboratories which are operated by a team of qualified doctors and efficient technicians, who provide results which are world-class, with a quality assurance. Blood samples for laboratory investigations are collected with the use of vacutainer system of collection, which helps in avoiding contamination and, thus, gross errors. Laboratories also provide services round-the-clock.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt">The Biochemistry Department is equipped with a new generation laboratory, which is further backed by a qualified and motivated team of doctors and technical staff. Equipped with the latest technology, the department not only performs routine biochemical tests, but also a wide variety of super specialized investigations which include therapeutic drug monitoring, including tacrolimus, cyclosporine, immunoglobulin, iron deficiency panel, stone analysis, diabetic profile, Wilson&rsquo;s Disease, pre-liver transplant work-up and many more.</span></p>\r\n',
