    doctor_brief:
      '<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr. Nigel is having an international experience in treating brain tumours, degenerative spine disease, disc replacement surgery, skull base surgery, and atlantoaxial fusions, Dr. Nigel Symss is a highly experienced neurosurgeon in Southern India, with over 26 years of clinical experience and over 15 years of experience in spinal and cranial surgery. He is currently employed at Gleneagles Global Health City in Chennai as a Senior Consultant Neurosurgeon and Functional Neurosurgeon. He is also a Senior Consultant in Neurosurgery at Fortis Malar Hospital in Chennai. Dr. Symss earned his MBBS in 1993 from Bangalore Medical College in Bangalore, and his DNB - Neurosurgery from the National Board of Examination in 2005. He has performed over 3500 neurosurgeries and has received a fellowship in functional neurosurgery from Flinders Medical Centre in Australia. He is a functional neurosurgery expert with international experience. Dr Symss specialises in Functional Neurosurgery, Paediatric Neurosurgery, Skull Base Neurosurgery, Spinal Neurosurgery, and Neuro-oncology Surgery. Dr Symss has conducted extensive research on hydrocephalus, which has been published in a number of prestigious journals. He is also on the editorial board of the Journal of Neuroendoscopy and International Journal of Hydrocephalus. Dr. Symss is renowned for his patient-centered approach and high success rate. Before performing any procedure, the doctor thoroughly assesses the patient&#39;s condition in order to understand the risks involved. With vast experience in performing even the most complex cases with high precision and accuracy, the doctor follows medical protocols in order to ensure patient safety. In addition, the doctor is up to date on the most recent techniques.</span></p>\r\n',
