    doctor_brief:
      '<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr. Muruganandham is famously known as &ldquo;the doctor who performed the first kidney transplantation surgery&rdquo;, Dr. Muruganandham K is an experienced and renowned urological surgeon, presently working as senior consultant and head of urology at Gleneagles Global Health City, Chennai, Dr. Muruganandham Khas extensive hands-on experience in all major areas of urology from leading Indian medical institutions such as SGPGIMS, Lucknow, and JIPMER, Puducherry, as well as focused training from CMC, Vellore, and MPUH, Nadiad, Gujarat. He received his medical degree from Thanjavur Medical College. He later earned his diploma in General Surgery after completing his master&#39;s degree in General Surgery at the Jawaharlal Institute of Postgraduate Medical Education and Research (JIPMER). Dr. Muruganandham also holds a master&#39;s degree in urology from the Sanjay Gandhi Postgraduate Institute of Medical Sciences. Minima Access Surgeons of India also awarded Dr. Muruganandham a fellowship in minimal access surgery. In his experience of more than 19 years, he has worked in clinical along with an academic profile in the field of general surgery, urology and renal transplant. Also, he is well-known for being a &quot;simple, best, and patient-friendly doctor.&quot; He is well-known and has expertise in the treatment of kidney stones, prostate-related disorders, kidney cancer, prostate cancer, bladder cancer, testicular cancer, penile cancer, urinary dribbling and in continence, urethral stricture disease, and male sexual dysfunction and infertility. He is a skilled kidney transplant, laparoscopic (keyhole), and endoscopic (laser) surgeon who provides phenomenal results to his patients.He was instrumental in establishing the renal transplantation programme and performed the first kidney transplantation surgery at JIPMER on March 3, 2012, under the supervision of the CMC, Vellore team. On July 10, 2013, he led the kidney transplant surgical team at JIPMER and successfully performed the first keyhole donor kidney retrieval and the first ever deceased donor kidney transplantation in the Union territory of Puducherry on December 5, 2013. He has served as a guest faculty member for numerous CMEs, conferences, and live operative workshops. He has given invited talks on laparoscopic urology and kidney transplantation at regional and national conferences. He was invited to perform and demonstrate laparoscopic donor nephrectomy and was instrumental in starting the programs at reputed medical institutions like SRMC, Porur, Chennai and SVIMS and Tirupathi.</span></p>\r\n',
