      '<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr. Narendra Kumar Pandey is the Chairman and Managing director of the Asian Institute of Medical Sciences.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">International College of Surgeons, Vice President, Chicago.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">International College of Surgeons, Chicago, Council Member.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Editor-in-Chief of the Indian Journal of Surgery.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Indian Health Care Federation Secretary.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Former President of the Indian Association of Surgeons.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr. Pandey did his internships in surgery and orthopaedics at the Ashford Hospital in London and the Aberystwyth District General Hospital and North Devon District Hospital in Aberystwyth, respectively. He also worked at Barnstable&#39;s District Hospital.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">He worked at Hammersmith Hospital, Kings College Hospital, Charing Cross Hospital, and Middle Sex Hospital in the United Kingdom. During his time in the United Kingdom, he was able to work and study under a number of prominent surgeons, including Sir Alfred Patrick M. Forrest, Professor Mansel, Professor Blumgart, and Professor Russell, and gain experience in liver and pancreatic surgery as well as limited access surgery.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">In 1984, he returned to India and began working as a consultant at Fortis Escorts Hospital in Faridabad, where he remained until 2007, when he left as the hospital&#39;s executive director. During that period, he also served on the board of directors of the Fortis Escorts Heart Institute in Delhi. By this time, he had made up his mind to open his own medical centre, and in 2010, he established the Asian Institute of Medical Sciences.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',
