      '<p><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr. Avi Kumar, who studied Tuberculosis and Respiratory Medicine or Pulmonary Medicine, is currently employed as a Consultant in Pulmonology, Chest, and Sleep Medicine at Fortis Escorts Heart Institute in New Friends Colony, Delhi.Dr. Kumar is particularly interested in and knowledgeable about India&#39;s most difficult therapies. He has completed his MBBS MD - Tuberculosis &amp; Respiratory Medicine or Pulmonary Medicine as well as a number of other medical studies from the Institution which is run by the University of Delhi and is wholly supported by the Indian government&#39;s Ministry of Health and Family Welfare.He enrolled at the above-mentioned famous university after passing the Delhi PG Medical Entrance Examination in 2006, and completed a three-year postgraduate residency programme in pulmonary medicine. The residency curriculum included intensive training in outpatient and inpatient management of tuberculosis and other respiratory disorders, emergency ward management, respiratory critical care medicine, and sleep medicine, among other academic and clinical activities. Working in several departments and laboratories was also part of the training.He has an excellent academic record and has gotten numerous medals and accolades for his achievements. The doctor is known for his warm demeanour and ability to immediately put patients at ease.</span></p>\r\n',
