    doctor_brief:
      '<p><span style="font-size:11pt">The surgeon to have successfully performedIndia&#39;s first heart-kidney combined transplant &amp; heart transplant, Dr.Alla Gopala Krishna Gokhale is a leading Cardiothoracic Surgeon in Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh. He is a Padma Shri recipient with an experience of over 34 years as a Cardio Thoracic Surgeon. He is presently practicing at Apollo Hospitals, Jubilee Hills, Hyderabad.</span></p>\r\n',
    doc_rating: "5",
    doc_education:
      '<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">MS, MCH, DNB, SMP &amp;Dsc</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">1982 - MBBS - Guntur Medical College, Guntur.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">1985 - MS - General Surgery - Guntur Medical College, Guntur.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">1990 - MCh - Cardio Thoracic Surgery - The Tamil Nadu Dr. M.G.R. Medical University (TNMGRMU).</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">1990 - DNB - Cardiothoracic Surgery - DNB board, New Delhi.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',
    doc_specialization: "1",
    doctor_experience:
      '<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Senior Consultant Cardiothoracic Transplant &amp; Minimal Access Surgeon</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">He is currently practicing as Cardiothoracic, Transplant and Minimal Access Cardiac Surgeon at Apollo Hospitals, Jubilee hills, Hyderabad.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr. Gokhale has also worked at Yashoda Hospitals, Secunderabad (2012-2015).</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Global Hospitals (2003-2012)</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Medicity Hospitals (1996-2003)</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">From 1995 to 1996, he did Fellowship at Barnes-Jewish Hospital, St Louis, USA, with Dr. Nicholas Kouchoukos and gained experience in the areas of redo coronary artery bypass surgery and aortic aneurysm surgeries and root repairs.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">From 1993 to 1995 he worked as a Fellow in cardiothoracic surgery at Westmead Hospital, Sydney.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">1992-93, he did fellowship in Heart Transplantation and Lung Transplantation at St Vincent&rsquo;s Hospital,&nbsp; Sydney, Australia</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">NIMS (1990-92).</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">During 1990 he was trained in cardiothoracic and vascular surgery at Christian Medical College Hospital, Vellore, and obtained M.Ch and DNB degrees</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">(1976&ndash;1985) Dr.Alla Gopala Krishna Gokhale obtained his MBBS and MS (General Surgery) from Guntur Medical College, India</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',
    treatment_list: "",
    hospital_awards:
      '<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">He holds the distinction of performing India&#39;s first heart-kidney combined transplant as well as the first heart transplant for a 69-year-old patient (oldest man to undergo heart transplant in India).</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">He is India&#39;s first heart surgeon to successfully perform heart and lung transplants. Dr. Gokhale performed the first successful heart transplant, lung transplant, and ventricular assist device implantation as a bridge to heart recovery in the states of Telangana and Andhra Pradesh.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr. Gokhale performed 29 heart transplants, 3 lung transplants, and over 15,000 open heart surgeries, both adult and paediatric, with a 98.4 percent success rate.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr.Alla Gopala Krishna Gokhale pioneered the art of Minimally Invasive Cardiothoracic Surgery for patients requiring multiple bypass grafts (key hole bypass surgery), valve replacements, and heart hole closure.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">He is the Founder Secretary of the Heart Failure Society in India, and he promotes the education of heart specialists in the management of patients with heart failure. Currently serving as President of the Indian Society for Heart and Lung Transplantation.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Dr. Gokhale received the Padma Shri, the country&#39;s fourth highest civilian award, in 2016, in addition to numerous awards from social and professional organisations.</span></li>\r\n\t<li><span style="font-size:11pt">Sahrudaya Health,Medical, and Educational Trust was established as a non-profit organisation by Dr. Gokhale. He is also establishing an open heart surgery programme at Government General Hospital, Guntur, his alma matter, on a PPP model with the Government of Andhra Pradesh. Nearly 500 open heart surgeries and three heart transplants were performed at that government hospital.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',
