      "<p>Neurosurgery is a medical specialty that deals with the diagnosis and treatment of the nervous system (brain, spinal cord ) and peripheral nerves within all parts of the body.&nbsp; The common name for Neurosurgery is Brain Surgery, but it is more than that.&nbsp; It deals with the diagnosis, prevention, surgical treatment of the Brain, Spinal cord, Peripheral Nervous system (disorders).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Nervous System&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nervous system is a network inside the human body that plays an essential role in everything you do like movements, hearing, breathing, listening, touching, digestion, regulating blood flow, blood pressure, breathing, blinking of eyes, maintaining body temperature.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nervous system is the command center of the body system that also controls complex processes like thoughts, memory.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parts of Nervous System&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The nervous system has two parts &ndash;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Central Nervous System and Peripheral Nervous System&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Central Nervous System</strong>&nbsp;&ndash;CNS is made of the brain and spinal cord and it controls major functions of the body and mind both.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Peripheral Nervous System</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; PNS is made of nerves that consist of nerves that branch from the CNS to the entire body. The information is carried from the brain, spinal cord to the body&rsquo;s organs, arms, legs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Difference Between Neurosurgeon and Neurologist</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Both neurosurgeons and neurologists could perform complex neurological investigations like MRI scans, CT scans, PET scans, EEG.&nbsp;<br />\r\nNeurologists are specialist who diagnoses and treats disorders of the brain and nervous system with symptoms like Chronic headache, Balance difficulties, Fatigue muscles. A neurosurgeon can only administer drugs as a treatment and refer to a Neurosurgeon for surgical procedures.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neurosurgeons are specialist who performs surgeries on people with chronic disorders that impair the normal functioning of the Nervous system. They perform surgeries like Disc removal, Brain&nbsp; Tumor removal, Spinal cord surgery.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neurosurgery is an advanced form of surgery and requires long-term training, experience, and precision in surgical procedures.&nbsp;Neurosurgery cost in India is comparatively affordable and cheaper than in other countries in the world.</p>\r\n",
