    treatment_faqs:
      '<p><strong>&nbsp;What are the Types of Surgeries Performed by Neurosurgeons in India?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are various procedures performed by Neurosurgeons in India providing successful surgeries with minimum or no complication.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The procedures include &ndash;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Microdiscectomy&nbsp;</strong>&ndash; It is the most common surgical procedure performed by Neurosurgeons. The Surgical procedure includes the removal of a disc that is compressing the nerve. The recovery is very fast and the patient is symptom-free within a few days.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Spinal Nerve Decompression</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Pain, stiffness in the back and neck is the most common symptom with spinal nerve Decompression. Firstly the patient is treated with Medicines and Therapies like exercises to strengthen the back and muscles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the patient is not relieved Spinal nerve decompression surgery is performed by Neurosurgeon. Post-surgery follow-up visits are important.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Craniotomy for a Brain tumor</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; This surgical procedure is complex and includes the opening of the skull to remove a brain tumor. This surgery is also useful in Epilepsy, Blood vessel diseases.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Do Neurosurgeons in India perform Minimally Invasive Spine surgeries?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Minimally invasive spine surgery includes the surgical procedure in which a small cut of about half an inch is made through the skin. Working and performing the surgery through this small incision helps in less damage to nearby tissues and muscles thus quick recovery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, the<a href="https://medsurgeindia.com/relevant-questions-to-ask-before-you-go-for-a-neurosurgery/">&nbsp;Neurosurgeons in India</a>&nbsp;perform Minimally invasive spine surgeries which have multiple benefits like less postoperative pain, Early discharge from hospital, early recovery, no blood loss, Fewer chances of getting infection post-surgery, and resuming daily activities very quickly.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Prevention Of Neurological Disorders&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Few events like accidents, trauma, burns, injuries are not under control but still, Neurological disorders could be controlled and prevented by following &ndash;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Regular exercise like cycling, brisk walking is important to maintain blood flow and keep the body fit and healthy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Control your lifestyle disorders like High blood pressure, Diabetes by regular monitoring for the same respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Keep a check on alcohol intake.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Completely avoid smoking or chewing tobacco.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. A healthy, fiber-rich diet like fruits and vegetables regularly maintains the healthy body thus the nervous system and its function.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep yourself hydrated with an intake of plenty of water and fresh fruits juices.</p>\r\n',
