      '<h2><strong>Before Procedure</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The surgeon ascertains general health of patient , past medical ,surgical history, also discusses the procedure its advantages and possible complications before the surgery. Blood tests, X-ray, MRI scan. Some medications like blood thinners need to be stopped at least 2 weeks before surgery. Advised to stop smoking as it decreases blood circulation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>During Procedure</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The procedure may be done through different techniques. It can be done as an open procedure or as&nbsp;<a href="https://medsurgeindia.com/cost/minimally-invasive-spine-surgery-cost-in-india/">minimally invasive spine surgery</a>, depending on the patient&rsquo;s needs and the surgeon&rsquo;s competence. To establish a path to the spine, an incision is made in the skin and tissues are gently pulled aside. Minimally invasive spine surgery is a technique that reduces the amount of damage to the tissue surrounding the operation site, allowing for a speedier recovery. A catheter is inserted into the tumour location to inject an embolic agent that blocks the vessels supplying the tumour, thereby limiting bleeding. Procedure performed under general anaesthesia. The nerve roots can be exposed and the dura can be identified using the posterior approach. For malignancies in the front of the spine, the anterior approach is used. The incisions are stitched up with sutures or staples following the treatment and are removed 10-14 days later.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>After Procedure</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For the next 3-5 days, you will be monitored in the&nbsp;<a href="https://medsurgeindia.com/hospital-department/oncology-and-oncosurgery/">hospital</a>. Following surgery, you will experience some pain that will be managed with medicine. Antibiotics will be given to you. In most cases, bed rest is not required. You will begin exercises with the assistance of a physical therapist. Smoking is not permitted. Smoking delays healing. It is suggested that you live a healthy lifestyle. Depending on the method, spinal surgery recovery can take weeks or even months.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Complications</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As in any surgery, there can be complications:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pain Bleeding Chances of blood clots (DVT) Infection Temporary loss of sensation Nerve damage- Any operation on the spine comes with the risk of damaging the nerves or spinal cord Damage can cause numbness or even paralysis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To know about the Best Spine Surgeons in India, click here.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Prognosis</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It depends on the type of spinal tumour, whether benign or malignant, primary or metastatic, as well as the patient&rsquo;s age and overall health.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Warning Signs after Procedure</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Redness, swelling Drainage from the incision site Tenderness chills Elevated temperature</p>\r\n',
