    id: 78,
    treatment_name: "Chemotherapy",
    specilization_id: "2",
    treatment_brief:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">Leukaemia is the cancer of blood-forming tissues including the bone marrow and obstructs the ability of the body to fight against infections. Various symptoms for the identification of leukemia include getting tired easily, pale skin tone, fever, easy bleeding, easy bruising and nosebleeds, bone or joint pain, swollen lymph nodes in the neck, underarms, groin, or stomach, frequent infections,&nbsp; weight loss, shortness of breath, night sweats and little energy and weakness. Lymphoblastic leukemia, acute myeloid leukemia, and chronic lymphocytic leukemia are the types of leukemia that can be treated through different treatment options available including radiation therapy, immunotherapy, targeted therapy, chemotherapy and hematopoietic cell transplant (bone marrow transplant). Chemotherapy is the most common form of treatment for cancer including most types of Leukemia as well. It aims at destroying cancer, prolonging life or relieving its symptoms by shrinking tumors that cause pain through variable combinations of medicines/ potent drugs or chemicals.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Procedure for Treatment</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">You may receive chemotherapy at home, in a doctor&rsquo;s office or in a hospital. Based on the type and stage of the blood cancer, the patients receive chemotherapy by mouth, as a cream, through a catheter, or intravenously (through an IV). Some chemotherapy drugs are taken in the form of capsules, some are given by inserting a tube with a needle into a vein or into a device in a vein in your chest. The treatment is cyclic - you can get it every day, week, or month. The body of the patient is given sufficient time to heal, strengthen and build healthy cells. A basic chemo regimen lasts for 5 minutes to 8 or more hours. Deciding the dosage of chemotherapy can be problematic - a low dosage could be ineffective and the toxicity of high dosage could be intolerable for the patient. Due to the lack of a better option, the BSA formula has been adopted since 1950 to determine the adequate dosage for chemotherapy. Measuring the blood levels in the blood plasma over time according to a formula or algorithm can help in achieving optimal exposure. Dosing is personalized to achieve target exposure and optimal results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Chemotherapy is an undoubtedly effective treatment but has many side effects, the most common being the destruction of fast-dividing cells of the body - cells lining the mouth, stomach and intestines and blood cells resulting in side effects like nausea, extreme hair fall, vomiting and fatigue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The cycle of Chemotherapy varies from once every week or once every three weeks. The treatment may go up to three to four months but the doctor will adjust the timings according to your situation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The patients with AML (Acute Myeloid Leukemia) and ALL (Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia) usually receive the treatment in two phases:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">1. Induction therapy-Patients go through various cycles of treatment in the hospital and will spend four to six weeks undergoing the therapy. Induction therapy attempts to kill as many AML and ALL cells as possible with chemotherapy and to get rid of any signs of disease left in the body. It also aims at bringing back the blood count of the body to normal. One cycle generally consists of a week of receiving drugs followed by many weeks of recovery and resting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">2. Post Remission Therapy-After the completion of Induction therapy, patients still need to undergo additional therapy which is post remission therapy, also known as consolidation therapy. If you skip this step, chances of the cancer returning are high. The therapy includes chemotherapy and a sometimes a stem transplant as well. Its purpose is to destroy the stray leukemic cells not found by any blood or marrow tests. You can get this done in a hospital or an outpatient setting over a period of four to six weeks or longer depending upon the treatment and it&rsquo;s side-effects. The overall health and the availability of a stem cell donor determine the type of post-remission therapy that patients need.</p>\r\n',
    treatment_doctors: "",
    treatment_faqs:
      '<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Q.1. How much does chemotherapy cost?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Ans.</strong> Depending on the type of cancer, the place of treatment, it can cost anywhere between Rs.2,00,000 - Rs.7,00,000.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Q2. How long does chemotherapy last?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Ans.&nbsp;</strong>It depends on various factors including the type of cancer, the kind of chemo used and the reaction of the body to the treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Q3. How does chemotherapy work?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>&nbsp;Ans.&nbsp;</strong>Chemotherapy works by destroying the growth of fast multiplying cancer cells through the use of various medicines.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Q4. Which drugs are used to cure most forms of Leukemia?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Ans.&nbsp;</strong>A combination of Cytarabine and an anthracycline drug, such as daunorubicin (daunomycin) or idarubicin is used to treat AML. Other chemo drugs that can be used to cure Leukemia include Cladribine (2-CdA), Mitoxantrone and Hydroxyurea.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Q5. How long does chemo treatment take?</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify"><strong>Ans.&nbsp;</strong>It is typically divided into three phases &ndash; Induction, Consolidation and Maintenance. Induction and Consolidation are intensive and last about a month and a few months respectively and Maintenance is less intensive &ndash; lasting for around two years.</p>\r\n',
    treatment_location: "",
    page_slug: "chemotherapy",
    meta_title: "Chemotherapy",
