    treatment_name: "Colorectal Surgery",
    specilization_id: "14",
    treatment_brief:
      '<p style="text-align:justify">Colorectal surgery is a procedure that is associated with the treatment of pathologies such as Ulcerative colitis, Crohn&rsquo;s disease, any mechanical obstruction, recurrent diverticulitis, colon cancer. It is highly invasive and risky surgery with long stay in the hospital after the surgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Procedure for Colorectal Surgery </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The various colorectal surgeries performed include</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Colectomy</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Colostomy</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Endoscopic Surgery</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Hemorrhoidectomy</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Ileal pouch anal anastomosis</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Resection</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Inflammatory Bowel Disease Surgery</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Rectopexy</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Internal spinchterotomy</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Preparation before the surgery</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Intravenous line is given in the arm to give any medication. Urinary catheter is connected to drain the urine and fluid from the body.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Colectomy</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Colectomy is a surgical procedure to remove all or some parts of the large intestine. The procedure starts with making a vertical incision into the abdomen area and the segment where the disease is present is reached. The diseased segment of the bowel is then removed, and &nbsp;the ends of the bowel are then anastomosed to be water tight that helps in healing process. This is known as segmental Colectomy. The removal of cancerous polyp from the colon or rectum region using colonoscope is known as Polypectomy. It is performed by inserting a Colonoscope into the rectum region. After that a wire loop is passed through the Colonoscope. The wire loop inserted will remove the polyp. There is another procedure of Colectomy that involves complete removal of the colon. It is performed in case of diseases such as ulcerative colitis.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Colostomy</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">The procedure starts making anaesthesia to the patient to relieve the discomfort and pain. Then a small hole is created in the abdominal wall. Then through this hole created one end of the colon that is affected is pulled out. At the new site of the opening, the waste will exit the body,a bag is attached and the bag will collect the waste material.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Ileal pouch anal anastomosis </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">This procedure restores the stool function when the large intestine of the patient is removed.In this procedure, the large intestine of the patient are removed followed by creating a pouch from the small intestine. Two surgeries are performed in this.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Inflammatory Bowel disease </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Before the procedure starts, tests for anaemia or any kind of infection is performed. Stool samples are taken to check for parasite in the infection. It can be carried out by<strong> </strong>Colonoscopy,</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Flexible sigmoidoscopy, Upper endoscopy, Capsule endoscopy and balloon assisted enteroscopy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Complications of colorectal surgery </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Complications arising from the colorectal surgery are postoperative and intraoperative. The post operative complications include space infections, ileus and bowel infection.Intraoperative complicationsinclude bleeding bowel injury, urethral lesions and bladder injuries.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style="text-align:justify"><strong>Post operative instructions that enhance the recovery after the surgery are</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Proper counselling of the patient</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">Minimising the IV fluidduring hospitalisation</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align:justify">To avoid opioid pain medication</p>\r\n',
    treatment_doctors: "",
    treatment_faqs:
      '<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Q.1. What is the duration of the colorectal surgery?</span></strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif"><strong>Ans. </strong>Colorectal surgery takes around 3 hours long to complete. It may take longer depending upon the procedure.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Q.2. Can colorectal surgery be fatal?</span></strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif"><strong>Ans. </strong>Compared to other surgical procedures, colorectal surgery is associated with high risk of morbidity and mortality.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Q.3. Colorectal surgery is a major or a minor surgery?</span></strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif"><strong>Ans. </strong>Colorectal surgery is a major surgical procedure.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Q.4. How long does it take to recover from the colorectal surgery?</span></strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif"><strong>Ans. </strong>It usually takes around two complete for a patient to recover completely after the colorectal surgery. Although the patient can walk and eat after 2 weeks of the surgery.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><strong><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">Q.5. How long does it take for the bowels of the patient to become normal after the colorectal?</span></strong></span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif"><strong>Ans. </strong>It takes around 4-5 days for the patient to have bowel movement after the surgery.Passing gas is the sign that patient&rsquo;s bowel are returning to normal.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',
    treatment_location: "",
    page_slug: "colorectal_surgery",
    meta_title: "Colorectal Surgery",
